# Retrospective logs are append-mostly. When two branches each add a different
# entry, a normal 3-way merge conflicts: on `retrospectives.md` at the shared
# top-of-file insertion (entries are prepended, newest-first), and on
# `retrospectives-archive.md` at the shared end-of-file insertion (pruned
# entries are appended). Both conflicts are verified, not theoretical. The
# built-in `union` merge driver keeps BOTH sides' added lines instead of
# conflicting — the right outcome for a lessons log (never lose a retro to a
# merge). A transient over-cap on retrospectives.md self-heals on the next
# append, which re-prunes to the cap and archives the overflow.
retrospectives.md          merge=union
retrospectives-archive.md  merge=union
